Home Owners Association

- At the Town Hall meeting it was mentioned about the possible need to create a separate HOA

- In further conversation with the AB Federation of Rural Water Co-ops we do not need to create a separate HOA, the Co-op can do everything.

Should we continue with investigating the acquisition of the common space & roadway?

- Concerns - sale of Barn Dance 

- New owner could develop Block 4 (triangle greenspace in the middle of lots 24 to 43) and fire-pit area as additional campground

- New owner could deny access to use pond

- New owner could deny our maintaining of greenspaces & roadway

- New owner could enforce Restrictive Covenants

- If we wanted to purchase in future, cost may be much more

- Costs: 

- Purchase price - $1.00 (Free but legal requirement for a cost)

- Survey cost and fees to transfer title: $13,000 (approx. $309 / lot)

- Ongoing cost estimates

- Property tax – estimated $500/yr (approx. $12 / lot per year)

- Insurance – less than $100/yr (approx. $3 / lot per year)

- Included in negotiations with Trevor (Barn Dance)

- Legal easement for access to pond

- Maintain pond level (as long as UID has water)

- Restrictive Covenants transferred to Co-op or removed

- A motion was brought forward to vote on purchasing the Roadway & Common Space, however, in further discussion it was agreed to conduct the vote on whether to continue the investigating of an acquisition and given that this is a significant cost we would email all owners about this item and get a vote from them, despite having a quorum of members in this meeting.

Vote to continue with investigating the acquisition of the common space & roadway?

	Vote Results: 14 in favour, 1 not in favour – **Motion ****Carried**

Should we look to create a Seasonal fee structure?

- An example of a three rate structure (seasonal, non-resident, resident) was presented.

- I would be difficult to police who can or cannot visit their lot

- What about Airbnb/VRBO properties?

- The difference in fees, in the example, from a one fee rate for a seasonal is $38.

Vote to look into a Fee structure based on usability

Vote Results: 1 in favour, 13 not in favour – **Motion ****Defeated**

 2021 Budget & Fees was presented

- For the Fees, 4 options were given based on whether to include Snow Removal costs and purchasing a new fountain.

- Snow Removal – over the last 2 years we have spent about $1500 per calendar year.  We have a quote from Chris Spokes to provide snow removal for the 21/22 winter season at $2,000 (we are clarifying details) or we have a contractor out of Pincher Creek @ $450 per callout, but during a heavy snowfall he may not come for a couple of days. Having a local person is ideal, but there is a concern whether he can handle a heavy snowfall and if not then who is responsible for the additional cost if he has the ‘contract’.

- Fountain – cost to purchase a new fountain like the one we had is $2,200

Vote to select a Budget option.

Vote Results: 

- A – With Snow Removal / with new fountain - 6

- B – Without Snow Removal / with new fountain - 0

- C – With Snow Removal / without new fountain - 8

- D – Without Snow Removal / without new fountain - 1

Budget option C **Carried**

Meeting adjourned: 2:56pm